<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,420,1904,1931]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Cymbopleura deqinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Y.-L. Li 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[527,613,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[629,742,1904,1930]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–20" captionStart-1="FIGURES 21–28" captionStart-2="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId-0="2.[136,243,1311,1333]" captionStartId-1="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionStartId-2="4.[136,243,1417,1439]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,422,1283]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetBox-2="[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetId-0="figure-140@2.[151,1436,422,1283]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetId-2="figure-94@4.[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–20. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., LM, DIC. Valve views, showing size range and variability of the holotype population. Scale bar = 10 μm." captionText-1="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." captionText-2="FIGURES 29–33. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, internal views. 29, 30. Internal view of entire valve. 31, 32. Detail of valve apices with prominent helictoglossa deflected to the dorsal side. 33. Detail of the valve central area showing the intermissio is lacking. Scale bar = 2 μm (Figs 29–30), 1 μm (Figs 31–33)." pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Figs 1–33</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
