<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1940,2074]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,401]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,365,1940,1966]" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Description:—</emphasis>
LM (
<figureCitation box="[423,542,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–20" captionStartId="2.[136,243,1311,1333]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,422,1283]" captionTargetId="figure-140@2.[151,1436,422,1283]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–20. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., LM, DIC. Valve views, showing size range and variability of the holotype population. Scale bar = 10 μm." pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Figs 1–20</figureCitation>
): Valves linear-lanceolate, commonly asymmetrical about the apical axis, dorsal and ventral margins similarly arched or occasionally parallel, apices rostrate to subcapitate bent in opposite directions. Length 27–31 um, width 6.0–7.5 um, length/width ratio varying between 3.8–4.7, median 4.3 (n=30). Raphe slightly lateral, narrowing towards the distal and proximal ends. External central raphe ends deflected gently towards the ventral side and tipped with slightly inflated pores. External terminal raphe fissures hooked towards dorsal margin. Axial area very narrow, linear or slightly broader towards the central area, approximately in the median line of the valve. Central area rectangular to elliptical, almost asymmetrical and then more well-developed dorsally or ventrally, occupying 1/3–1/2 of the valve width, with 2–3 markedly shortened central dorsal striae, and 3–4 slightly shortened central ventral striae, occasionally lacking or not well expressed. Striae radiate more strongly towards the apices, indistinctly punctate-lineate, more widely spaced at the valve centre dorsally, density 
<quantity box="[1110,1210,338,364]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="3.556" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="16.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="14.0">14–18 in</quantity>
10 µm in the middle portion, up to 
<quantity box="[295,394,374,400]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" metricValueMax="5.588" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22 in</quantity>
10 µm towards the ends. Individual areolae not visible.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="2" pageNumber="235" startId="2.[136,243,1311,1333]" targetBox="[151,1436,422,1283]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1453,1311,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,303,1311,1333]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">FIGURES 1–20.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[308,623,1311,1333]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName authority="Meng &amp; Guo &amp; Zhang &amp; Kociolek &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Meng &amp; Guo &amp; Zhang &amp; Kociolek &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[308,545,1311,1332]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbopleura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="deqinensis" status="sp. nov.">Cymbopleura deqinensis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[550,623,1312,1333]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, LM, DIC. Valve views, showing size range and variability of the holotype population. Scale bar = 10 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1415,2090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
SEM: Valve exterior (
<figureCitation box="[426,555,1415,1442]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 21–28</figureCitation>
): Raphe undulate with proximal raphe ends dilated and slightly ventrally deflected near the valve centre (
<figureCitation box="[391,613,1451,1478]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 21, 22, 27, 28</figureCitation>
), terminal fissures hooked, deflected towards the dorsal side, terminating between shortened striae extending around the apices (
<figureCitation box="[746,877,1487,1514]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 21–26</figureCitation>
). Striae uniseriate, slightly radiate throughout (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 21–28</figureCitation>
). Areolae mostly round to elliptical, partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularly shaped along the axial area and central area, 
<quantity box="[283,384,1559,1586]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="35.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="30.0">30–40 in</quantity>
10 μm (
<figureCitation box="[482,615,1559,1586]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 21–28</figureCitation>
), with 8–10 areolae larger than the rest near the central area in size (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 27–28</figureCitation>
). No stigmata and apical pore fields present (
<figureCitation box="[715,847,1595,1622]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1269,1291]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,190,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,190,1244]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, external views. 21, 22. External view of an entire valve. 23, 26. Detail of valve apices showing, striae with rounded areolae and the distal raphe fissures. 27, 28. External view of valve centre showing the proximal raphe endings and larger areolae surrounding the central area, the black arrows in the figure indicate partly T-shaped, V-shaped or irregularlyshaped areolae, the white arrows in the figure indicate several larger areolae near the central area. Scale bar = 2 μm (Fig. 21), 1 μm (Figs 22–28)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 21–28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1415,2090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
Valve interior (
<figureCitation box="[361,494,1631,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1417,1439]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetId="figure-94@4.[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, internal views. 29, 30. Internal view of entire valve. 31, 32. Detail of valve apices with prominent helictoglossa deflected to the dorsal side. 33. Detail of the valve central area showing the intermissio is lacking. Scale bar = 2 μm (Figs 29–30), 1 μm (Figs 31–33)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 29–33</figureCitation>
): Striae formed by uniseriate, round areolae delimited by slightly oblique orientated vimines (
<figureCitation box="[239,370,1667,1694]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1417,1439]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetId="figure-94@4.[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, internal views. 29, 30. Internal view of entire valve. 31, 32. Detail of valve apices with prominent helictoglossa deflected to the dorsal side. 33. Detail of the valve central area showing the intermissio is lacking. Scale bar = 2 μm (Figs 29–30), 1 μm (Figs 31–33)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 29–33</figureCitation>
). Internal raphe slit continuous, without intermissio (
<figureCitation box="[958,1128,1667,1694]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1417,1439]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetId="figure-94@4.[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, internal views. 29, 30. Internal view of entire valve. 31, 32. Detail of valve apices with prominent helictoglossa deflected to the dorsal side. 33. Detail of the valve central area showing the intermissio is lacking. Scale bar = 2 μm (Figs 29–30), 1 μm (Figs 31–33)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 29, 30, 33</figureCitation>
). Terminal raphe ends offset, bent slightly towards the dorsal margin, and terminating in small, knob-like helictoglossae adjacent to the shortened striae (
<figureCitation box="[212,343,1739,1766]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1417,1439]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetId="figure-94@4.[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, internal views. 29, 30. Internal view of entire valve. 31, 32. Detail of valve apices with prominent helictoglossa deflected to the dorsal side. 33. Detail of the valve central area showing the intermissio is lacking. Scale bar = 2 μm (Figs 29–30), 1 μm (Figs 31–33)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 29–32</figureCitation>
). Stigmata absent (
<figureCitation box="[555,726,1739,1766]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1417,1439]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetId="figure-94@4.[177,1411,317,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Cymbopleura deqinensis sp. nov., SEM, internal views. 29, 30. Internal view of entire valve. 31, 32. Detail of valve apices with prominent helictoglossa deflected to the dorsal side. 33. Detail of the valve central area showing the intermissio is lacking. Scale bar = 2 μm (Figs 29–30), 1 μm (Figs 31–33)." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Figs 29, 30, 33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
